      • zIndex

        public int zIndex()
        Description copied from interface: Visible
        Gets the z-index for this object. Higher numbers mean this object is lower (farther from the camera), and lower numbers means it's higher (closer to the camera)

        Lower numbers are always rendered on top. Z=0 means it's an actor, Z=10 means it's a tile.
        Specified by:
        zIndex in interface Visible
        Returns:
        A number representing this object's z-index.
